Ken Strongman is a private commercial mediator/arbitrator of complex, high risk litigated cases since 2004.
As a full-time, mediator and arbitrator, Ken Strongman works to unite people into purposeful and unified directions, actions, and efforts by getting under surface appearances. By doing so, he facilitates the parties in developing their unique solutions. Disputes addressed include business, securities, construction defects, real estate, intellectual property, employment, environment, energy, and trusts &amp;amp; estates.

Ken Strongman has mediated full time since 2004. Besides an active mediation practice, he is a mediation trainer, and adjunct professor teaching and mentoring new mediators. He routinely speaks and writes on the subject as well.
